### **Phase 1 Conclusion**

Phase 1 delivered a fully operational phishing infrastructure with real external email delivery, per-victim tracking telemetry, and complete credential capture across two campaigns. Harvest #1 exposed genuine defensive mechanisms; Gmail's reputation-based spam filtering and Microsoft's retained client-side JavaScript validation and both documented as realistic findings. Harvest #2 addressed the validation blocker by replacing the cloned page with a custom HTML form, achieving full attack chain completion with both victims submitting credentials successfully.

Across both campaigns, Phase 1 demonstrates the iterative nature of real-world offensive operations: initial infrastructure deployment surfaces defensive signals, which an attacker analyses and adapts to in subsequent attempts. This attacker-defender loop (observe, adapt, re-execute) is the core methodology Phase 3 detection engineering will build against.

All telemetry generated across both campaigns serves as the artifact base for Phase 2 victim instrumentation and Phase 3 SIEM-based detection rule authoring.
